  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle, then peel and finely slice your <strong>brown onion[s]</strong></p><p>Peel and finely slice your<strong> garlic</strong></p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced onion</strong> and cook for 5 min or until softened</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1658828798288-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1658828798288-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1658828798288-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1658828798288-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1658828798288-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, wash your <strong>spinach</strong>, then add to a colander and pour <strong>boiled water</strong> all over it until it's wilted</p><p>Rinse the<strong> wilted spinach</strong> under <strong>cold</strong> <strong>running</strong> <strong>water</strong> until it's cool enough to handle</p><p>Once cool, squeeze as much water out of the spinach as you can then chop it roughly</p><p>Reboil a kettle</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1658828806554-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1658828806554-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1658828806554-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1658828806554-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1658828806554-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Chop your <strong>sweet potato[es] </strong>(skins on) into large, bite-sized pieces</p><p>Add the <strong>sliced garlic</strong>,<strong> ground fenugreek</strong>, <strong>garam masala</strong> and <strong>chilli flakes</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) to the softened onion and cook for 30 secs or until fragrant</p><p>Add the<strong> chopped sweet potato </strong>to the pan and cook for 3 min further or until starting to brown</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1658828822829-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1658828822829-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1658828822829-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1658828822829-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1658828822829-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the sweet potato is browning, dissolve your <strong>vegetable stock mix</strong>,<strong> tomato paste</strong> and 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [2 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar</strong> in 300ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[390ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[550ml]</span><strong> boiled water</strong> – this is your<strong> tomato stock</strong></p><p>Once the sweet potato has browned, add the <strong>tomato stock</strong> and<strong> chopped spinach </strong>to the pan</p><p>Reduce the heat to medium-low and cook, covered, for 12-15 min or until the sweet potato is fork-tender – this is your <strong>fragrant sweet potato saag masala</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1658828851485-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1658828851485-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1658828851485-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1658828851485-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1658828851485-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the sauce thickens, crush your <strong>cardamom pods</strong> open by squashing them with the side of a knife</p><p>Melt a knob of <strong>butter alternative</strong> in a pot with a matching lid over a medium heat</p><p>Once melted, add the <strong>crushed</strong> <strong>cardamom pods</strong> and <strong>star anise </strong>to the pot and cook for 30 secs or until fragrant</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1658828860919-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1658828860919-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1658828860919-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1658828860919-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1658828860919-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>basmati rice</strong> to the pot and cook for 1 min further, then add 250ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[325ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[500ml]</span><strong> cold</strong> <strong>water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 10-12 min or until all the water<strong> </strong>has been absorbed and the rice is cooked</p><p>Once cooked, remove from the heat and keep covered until serving – this is your <strong>pilau rice</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1658828879343-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1658828879343-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1658828879343-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1658828879343-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1658828879343-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the pilau rice is cooking, chop most of your <strong>coriander</strong> finely, including the stalks (save some leaves for garnish!)</p><p>Stir the <strong>chopped coriander</strong> through the <strong>pilau rice</strong>, discard the star anise and cardamom pods</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1658828892178-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1658828892178-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1658828892178-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1658828892178-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1658828892178-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>fragrant</strong> <strong>sweet potato saag masala </strong>with the <strong>pilau rice </strong>to the side</p><p>Garnish with the <strong>reserved</strong> <strong>coriander leaves</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
      "media": {
        "images": []
      }
    }
